<P>These effectually covered the Siege by cruising, two small <HI>French</HI> Vessels only got in by a Fog; and when it was resolved by the Sea and Land Officers, to storm Town <HI>Iune</HI> 18. the depended upon Attack was by Sea, while our Land Forces by Way of Diversion made a Feint (but without any practicable Breach) to storm it ashore; at that Time we had <HI>British</HI> Men of War
