all these may be called Line of Battle Ships; but in the Progress of this present <HI>French</HI> War to this Writing, they are reduced to near half the Number.</NOTE> reduc|ed, and not capable of sending any considerable Squadron so far abroad; perhaps in good Oeconomy and with suf|ficient Security; the present nominal chargeable Corps (besides the large Detachment from the Train or Ord|nance) in Garrison at <HI>Louisbourg</HI> of about 4000 Men, may be reduced to 2000 effective Men, and the reformed Men may with proper Encouragement be sent to settle, and be intermixed with the <HI>French</HI> in <HI>Nova Scotia</HI>&punc; continuing them in Corps and in Pay for some Time.</P>
<P>The present Garrison Troops of <HI>Louisbourg,</HI> if com|pleat, consist of
